          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "ganache emulsion",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp99alf40000qgv4l25nf4mo"
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Put the finely chopped {{dark-chocolate}} into a medium bowl. Heat the {{double-cream}} in a small saucepan until just steaming (do not let it boil). Pour the warm cream over the chocolate and let it sit for 1 minute. Start whisking small circles from the centre of the bowl outward; the emulsion forms first in the middle and spreads as you widen the circles. When the mixture is smooth and glossy, whisk in the {{unsalted-butter}}, {{vanilla-extract}} and {{sea-salt-fine}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Chill, roll, dust",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Press cling film onto the surface of the ganache and chill for 3 hours, or until firm enough to scoop. Sift the {{cocoa-powder}} into a shallow bowl. Scoop teaspoonfuls of ganache, roll quickly between cold palms into rough balls, then drop into the cocoa and roll to coat. Set on baking paper. Chill until firm. Keep refrigerated in an airtight box.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
